& [OperatorApprovedApplyPolicy] is the safety policy for applying ManualMergePacket output to a target workspace
  @ [governing_specification] specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  @ [manual_merge_policy] coordination/manual_merge_packet_policy.sop
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-29T23:30:00Z

  + [policy_status] is design_ready_not_executable
  + [authority_boundary] is apply_policy_not_apply_command
  + [default_behavior] is no_target_workspace_mutation
  + [purpose] is ensure target workspace application can only happen through explicit operator intent, path-checked packet evidence, rollback evidence, and post-apply verification

  = must: require an explicit operator command or flag before applying any packet
  = must: require manual_merge_packet.sop and merge_review_decision.sop from the same run root
  = must: require merge_review_decision is ready_for_manual_merge_review or manually_resolved
  = must: reject apply when merge_conflict_ledger.sop has unresolved conflicts
  = must: check every target path stays within target_workspace_root before writing
  = must: snapshot every existing target file before replacement or deletion
  = must: write an apply_plan.sop before file mutation
  = must: write an apply_result.sop after mutation attempt
  = must: run verification command after successful mutation
  = must: make rollback command available from apply_result.sop

  - never: apply by default during normal negotiation runs
  - never: apply when target_workspace_root is inferred from the current shell without packet evidence
  - never: apply if rollback snapshot creation fails
  - never: hide partially applied files after a failed apply

& [ApplyCommandContract] is the future explicit operator interface
  + [command_name] is apply-manual-merge-packet
  + [required_arg] is --run-root
  + [required_arg] is --target-workspace-root
  + [required_arg] is --i-understand-this-mutates-workspace
  + [optional_arg] is --dry-run
  + [optional_arg] is --verification-command
  + [default_mode] is dry_run
  + [mutation_mode] is enabled only by explicit mutation acknowledgement

& [ApplyPlan] is the pre-mutation evidence artifact
  + [field] is packet_ref
  + [field] is target_workspace_root
  + [field] is target_path_set
  + [field] is snapshot_plan
  + [field] is rollback_plan_ref
  + [field] is verification_command
  + [field] is manager_acceptance_ref
  + [field] is shaliach_review_ref
  + [field] is authority_boundary

& [ApplyResult] is the post-mutation evidence artifact
  + [field] is apply_status
  + [field] is applied_file_set
  + [field] is skipped_file_set
  + [field] is snapshot_ref_set
  + [field] is rollback_command
  + [field] is verification_result_ref
  + [field] is error_summary
  + [field] is authority_boundary

& [RollbackCommandContract] is the future explicit rollback interface
  + [command_name] is rollback-manual-merge-packet
  + [required_arg] is --apply-result
  + [required_arg] is --target-workspace-root
  + [required_arg] is --i-understand-this-mutates-workspace
  + [default_mode] is dry_run
  + [mutation_mode] is enabled only by explicit rollback acknowledgement

& [ImplementationReadinessGate] is the minimum before building apply command code
  + [required] is ManualMergePacket path checks are tested
  + [required] is rollback snapshot path rules are tested
  + [required] is dry-run apply plan generation is tested
  + [required] is mutation mode requires explicit acknowledgement
  + [required] is failed verification records apply_result.sop without deleting snapshots
